First run at NCAA preseason rankings is below. Teams are projected using team level stats like their previous season's ranking and number of returning players, and player-level stats like the players' projected WinShares.

&nbsp;

[googleapps domain="docs" dir="spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vSqMIZTva9GVWzfAf028HsJiwHT0dEzxrmjoaiD_XRNMT3gCdZq0u5OiPajzSeP4-b53jgZUbMNF7Pm/pubhtml?widget=true&amp;amp;headers=false" /]

&nbsp;

The Value column is the team's projection, the Rank column is the projected rank, and LastKPOMRk is the team's 17/18 end of season KPOM Rank. The Value column in my rankings doesn't really have any meaning, but it is a more accurate predictor of team's rankings since it allows for things like ranking teams evenly instead of forcing things to be uniform like an ordinal ranking does. Code/data on <a href="https://github.com/dlm1223/ncaa-preseason/tree/master/Team%20Projections">github</a>.

update 6/4: noticed a couple bugs like players incorrectly being included in 2019 so some teams moved up/down a couple spots.

update 9/26: view up-to date team rankings <a href="https://www.brianlefevre.com/category/ncaab/">here</a>

